Commentary Text: Coulter-Nile to Glenn Phillips, out Bowled!! RR are making a proper mess of this game. This was a gentle length delivery on the leg stump, Phillips went back and across. They say you got to stay really low of low bounce wickets. Phillips did try that to an extent but he played too far across the line looking to pull and it went right through the legs. Didn't even hit the top of the stumps. Looks really bad on the replay when it goes through the legs. Glenn Phillips b Coulter-Nile 4(13)

Commentary Text: Neesham to Shivam Dube, out Bowled!! Neesham! The dugout is all smiles. RR need to show some maturity here. Dube was right with the thought of trying to reach out for this drive through cover because it was a very wide ball. But when that front foot doesn't go towards the ball and stays stuck as Dube does, it's difficult to get control and he ends up losing balance and dragging this onto the stumps. Commentary Text: Neesham to Samson, out Caught by Jayant Yadav!! Picked for the game and you get the opposition captain first ball. Can you please the management more? Absolutely irresponsible hack from Samson. This is not a pitch to be hitting on the rise, Samson tried to go more over cover because Ro had the field up even after the powerplay. Kudos to the MI captain. The bat turned in Sanju's hands and it flew low to point off the outer half of the bat. Sharp work at backward point diving forward. Neesham holding cross seam and then letting it out scrambled seam, got a bit of extra bounce and hit him high on the bat. Samson c Jayant Yadav b Neesham 3(6)

Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by (sub)Lomror!! In the air ... and ... taken! 127.9kph, it's the cutter from a good length and Suryakumar Yadav is through with his loft early. The bat turns at the point of impact and SKY has totally miscued it. Goes a long way up in the air and Lomror barely had to move at mid-off to gobble it up. In an attempt to finish the match quickly, Suryakumar perishes.
